{# acl_alert_email.j2 — plain-text OT ACL alert email body                     #}
{# Used as an alternative to inline body building in the alert task.            #}
{# Variables provided by illumio_ot__alert_network_team.yml                    #}
======================================================================
ILLUMIO OT ACL MONITOR — {{ ot_alert_event_type | default('EVENT') }}
======================================================================

{% if ot_alert_event_type | default('') == 'DETECTION' %}
New pending ACL objects have been detected in the Illumio PCE that
have NOT yet been provisioned (enforced). A network team member must
review these changes and run the deployment playbook to approve them.

Detection Summary
-----------------
PCE URL         : {{ pce_url }}
Organisation ID : {{ org_id }}
Detected at     : {{ ansible_date_time.iso8601 }}
New ACL objects : {{ ot_new_acl_count | default(0) }}

New Pending Items
-----------------
{% for item in ot_new_acl_items | default([]) %}
  {{ loop.index }}. {{ item.name | default('(unnamed)') }}
     HREF        : {{ item.href | default('N/A') }}
     Updated at  : {{ item.updated_at | default('N/A') }}
     Created by  : {{ item.created_by.href | default('N/A') }}
{% endfor %}

Pending Report
--------------
Full JSON report saved at:
  {{ ot_acl_pending_file | default(ot_artifacts_dir + '/acl_pending.json') }}

Next Steps
----------
  1. Review the pending report listed above.

  2. If changes are approved, run the deployment playbook:

       ansible-playbook illumio/playbooks/02_illumio_ot_acl_deploy.yml \
         -i illumio/inventory_ot --ask-vault-pass \
         -e "apply_changes=true"

  3. To promote rules to ACTIVE ENFORCEMENT (traffic affected):

       ansible-playbook illumio/playbooks/02_illumio_ot_acl_deploy.yml \
         -i illumio/inventory_ot --ask-vault-pass \
         -e "apply_changes=true promote_policy=true"

  4. If the detected changes are NOT authorised, investigate immediately.
     Contact the PCE administrator: {{ pce_url }}

{% elif ot_alert_event_type | default('') == 'DEPLOYMENT' %}
An OT ACL deployment has completed on the Illumio PCE.

Deployment Summary
------------------
PCE URL         : {{ pce_url }}
Organisation ID : {{ org_id }}
Operator        : {{ ansible_user_id }}
Completed at    : {{ ansible_date_time.iso8601 }}
Dry run only    : {{ dry_run | default(true) }}
Rules applied   : {{ apply_changes | default(false) }}
Policy promoted : {{ promote_policy | default(false) }}
ACLs processed  : {{ ot_acls | default([]) | length }}
ACLs applied    : {{ ot_acls_applied | default(0) }}

ACLs Processed
--------------
{% for acl in ot_acls | default([]) %}
  {{ loop.index }}. {{ acl.name }}
     Rule Set  : {{ acl.rule_set_name }}
     Services  : {{ acl.services | map(attribute='port') | list | join(', ') }}
     Ticket    : {{ acl.ticket_ref | default('N/A') }}
     Enabled   : {{ acl.enabled | default(true) }}
{% endfor %}

Policy Status
-------------
{% if apply_changes | bool and promote_policy | bool %}
  ACTIVE — rules are now enforced in the OT environment.
  Affected traffic is subject to the new segmentation policy.
{% elif apply_changes | bool %}
  DRAFT — rules have been written to PCE but are NOT yet enforced.
  Run the playbook again with promote_policy=true to enforce.
{% else %}
  DRY RUN — no changes were made to PCE policy.
  Run the playbook again with apply_changes=true to write rules.
{% endif %}

Artifacts
---------
  Deployment log : {{ ot_artifacts_dir }}/acl_apply_{{ ansible_date_time.date }}.json
{% if apply_changes | bool and promote_policy | bool %}
  Promotion log  : {{ ot_artifacts_dir }}/acl_promotion_{{ ansible_date_time.date }}.json
{% endif %}
{% endif %}

======================================================================
This alert was generated automatically by Ansible.
Playbook : illumio/playbooks/
PCE      : {{ pce_url }}
Host     : {{ ansible_hostname | default('localhost') }}
Do not reply to this email.
======================================================================
